prompt:
Eight delegates — Odell, Pasha, Quilla, Renn, Sable, Tazio, Ursa, and Vinn — are to be seated in a single row of 8 chairs numbered 1 through 8, one delegate per chair. Two chairs are ADJACENT exactly when their numbers differ by 1. A seating must satisfy ALL of the following constraints:
(a) Odell and Pasha do not sit in adjacent chairs;
(b) Quilla's chair number is lower than Renn's chair number;
(c) Sable sits in none of chairs 1, 2, or 8;
(d) Tazio and Ursa sit in adjacent chairs;
(e) the chair numbers of Vinn and Odell differ by exactly 2;
(f) Renn and Tazio do not sit in adjacent chairs.

How many distinct seatings satisfy all six constraints? Give the exact integer inside \boxed{}.

Consider strings of length 12 over the alphabet {0, 1, 2, 3}. Call a string ADMISSIBLE if it satisfies ALL FOUR conditions:
(a) every pair of adjacent characters differs by at most 1 in numeric value (so 0 may be followed by 0 or 1; 1 by 0, 1, or 2; 2 by 1, 2, or 3; 3 by 2 or 3);
(b) the string does NOT contain "010" as a contiguous substring;
(c) the string does NOT contain "232" as a contiguous substring;
(d) the first character and the last character are different.

How many admissible strings of length 12 are there? Give the exact integer inside \boxed{}.
